reviews.review_text: Took my parents to this restaurant, and I personally believe this to be the best Restaurant in Kerrisdale. The lobster with fried noodles is my favourite! The waiter is very quick and efficient and the Manager she is very friendly we have good conversations.
Good local restaurant known for seafood their seafood and deep fried dishes.

This has the yummiest lobster glass noddles. Fresh and delicious. We also had the Taiwanese  broccoli, salt and pepper prawns and seafood noodles. Even the mango pudding and melon were scrumptious. The owner and staff were friendly and welcoming. Large portions! Come hungry

We ordered takeout beef brisket noodle soup and sliced fish congee. We were previously going to East Van or Richmond for these Cantonese staples, but are so pleasantly surprised with the quality here. The beef brisket soup has good noodles, very tender and green veggies in it. The congee has the perfect texture and taste and a good portion size. Each soup was $14.50, which seems well worth it for the size. We will be back!

I honestly had some of the best take out food I have ever eaten here the other night. The food sure wasn t the standard fare I normally find. This was fresh. This was cooked properly. Not greasy. And most importantly...really really REALLY tasty! I see why they have been around for so long. Quality food!! Top shelf 5 Star!!
Food and service has been consistently rly excellent through all the years we have been going here! They also are very careful with food prep if you have food sensitivities or allergies-

Last minute orders from my master to pick up dinner and it was up to me from where and even though it was also there closing time they were accommodating, it was my first time to try them and it was a very good choice food was excellent.

Excellent seafood restaurant, the freshest seafood in town, the food is absolutely delicious, not the average Chinese restaurant, ask for menu recommendations from the owner, the service is very personal.
I love this place. Fantastic food and great staff. They go out of their way to make you feel safe during this pandemic.
Good service and quality here. Staff are engaged and attentive. The food is good value for the money spent. Delicious! Recommend.
Really good food and really nice people I dropped my glasses there and when I came back for them they had picked them up and cleaned them :)
Super delicious quality food, they have authentic Chinese food there
Delicious authentic Chinese cuisine highly recommend.
Pretty good place, I don t really understand the bad reviews.
Seating on Mothers day was fair. Food was good
Good food
Delicious traditional chinese food.
Best place ever
Parking: Nice Food
The ingredients are very fresh and the taste is very authentic. Compared with the surrounding shops, the serving size is much larger, and the food is served quickly enough.

The taste is very good, the king crab is amazing The glutinous rice chicken is also very unique. There are no shortcomings except that the price is a bit expensive   but it s worth the money! Recommended! Unfortunately, I forgot to take a photo
I think the glutinous rice chicken, king crab, and roasted pigeon are the best in Vancouver.
Sliced duck, king crab, and glutinous rice chicken are all delicious.
Very good
I like glutinous rice chicken so much
Tastes great
Good soup!
good service
World class Chinese food

Deducted one star because of delivery having a high dollar minimum. I cant understand the low rating for Loks. I have only had mediocre food from them once in over 20 years! Everything we order is delicious and properly cooked. The BEST beef in the beef and broccoli and the beef and rice noodle! Absolutely delicious - tender and juicy. They will also add extra beef for a fee and it is honestly worth every penny. Also. the spring rolls are really good and not just full of cabbage as so many are. We love Loks and wished they would lower their delivery $ minimum as its unrealistic for two people - min $60 I believe. The place is very clean, and they are taking the pandemic rules seriously and I value that tremendously. Loks for life for us :))
Great food, friendly service, and reliable.

Good authentic Chinese restaurant ran by friendly staffs and owner. Only warning I have is if youre going to try the king crab, make sure you have enough people to share... We have the smallest king crab available but it is still way way way too much for my wife and myself (since the kids arent big fan on crab)... Although the crab was really sweat and delicious.

Great Chinese food. Irene Loks family have been providing Kerrisdale (really, the whole Westside) with classics from your favorite Chinese menus--except better than anyone else. Top drawer service, too. Friendly and polite.

Great little place in the heart of Kerrisdale. My wife & I always get consistant quality of good food. We just love their take out orders and being able to swap out an item & exchange of something else.
Great food, friendly owner with good service. they do all-day menus for both take out and delivery which is great.
quite expensive,food is so so.
Good overall Chinese food.

The taste is good and the price is acceptable. The mutton stew is very rich. It is very comfortable to have it in the winter and drink it while it is hot. The black pepper beef cubes were well received by everyone at the table. Compared with other Chinese food, fried rice uses less ingredients and is not worth it.
The Cantonese food here is authentic, tastes great, and the seafood is fresh. It is a good place to eat.
The crispy duck is delicious

Jun 26 , 2023 Ive never been to this chinese restaurant in Kerrisdale , I passed by it several times but have not gone to order take out . I can imagine after reading some of the reviews , some good and some not so good. I might just try this restaurant out of curiosity for take out one time. I dont live in the area . Maybe after trying the food Ill get some idea how the food is really like Daryl , Burnaby
The food and service was good. But thought for what we paid for the amount of each of the servings were a little small compared to other Chinese restaurants.
Reasonable price and quality of food in Vancouver west side. Brisket Rice very yummy.
The food was pretty good when we ate here, but not as good when it was take out. Service can be better.
Food great, service was ok
The fish skin tastes good, you can try the new glutinous rice chicken
Food quality is okay, price is expensive

Food was ok but expensive and service is poor. Waiter was pushy when taking our order. Originally ordered half chicken but was told it was unavailable and was served a full order of duck instead - $20 difference in price for that one dish! Interior is extremely outdated. Will not be returning again. Food

Very forgettable with rude staff. We stopped for lunch, were seated without a word, had to ask for lunch menus and we served by a rather sullen, bored waiter. The food was not great, greasy and flavorless. I would most definitely not visit again. It seemed like we were treated differently than the Asian clientele seated in the restaurant.

Service was good. Food was good. This was the most expensive Chinese restaurant I have ever gone to. Did not find the portions  matched the price. Average to small sized servings. Lunch is better priced, supper too expensive for no clear reason.
